Yahaya Bello, Kogi State Governor and candidate of the All Progressives Congress, APC, in the ongoing governorship election, has defeated his closest rivals, Musa Wada of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, in his polling unit. Results from Bello’s polling unit indicated that the governor had 716 votes to defeat his top challangers, Wada and Natasha Akpoti of the Social Democratic Party, SDP, who had no votes The governor’s polling unit is Okene-Eba/Agassa/Ahache Ward, Unit 11, Okene Local Government Area of Kogi State. Results of other polling units are still being announced. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.